FBIS3-7955 "dreeu041_k_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Mar 1994 CROATIA Tudjman Welcomes Muslim-Croat Talks LD0103222094 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 2100 GMT 1 Mar 94 LD0103222094 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Text] [Announcer] Croatian President Franjo Tudjman returned from Albania this evening. At Zagreb Pleso airport the president was welcomed by Stipe Mesic, Josip Manolic, Nikica Valentic, Janko Bobetko, Gojko Susak, Jure Radic, and other top state officials. Following his arrival at the airport Tudjman told journalists that the talks he held in Tirana were useful for the political and economic development of Croatia and Albania. Commenting on a meeting between Foreign Minister Granic and Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic in Washington, President Tudjman said: [Begin recording] [Tudjman] I think that this is a success both for our policy and this time also for international policy, the European and U.S. ones. This is a success that is leading toward peace, which is most important, while it is opening up possibilities to Croatia for the resolution of all its problems, primarily the speedier resolution of problems regarding Croatian territories under UN protection -- in other words, under Serb occupation -- and the resolution of all other economic and financial problems, which is very important. [end recording]
